Based on my investigation of the Quarkus codebase, here are my findings:

## 1. Is `Optional<SomeBuildItem>` ever `null` in build steps?

**No — it is never `null`.** The Quarkus builder framework explicitly wraps the value using `Optional.ofNullable()`, which guarantees a non-null Optional.

**Evidence from `core/deployment/src/main/java/io/quarkus/deployment/ExtensionLoader.java`** (lines 354-358, 432-437, 606-611):
```java
} else if (isOptionalOf(parameterType, SimpleBuildItem.class)) {
    final Class<? extends SimpleBuildItem> buildItemClass = rawTypeOfParameter(parameterType, 0)
            .asSubclass(SimpleBuildItem.class);
    stepConfig = stepConfig.andThen(bsb -> bsb.consumes(buildItemClass, ConsumeFlags.of(ConsumeFlag.OPTIONAL)));
    ctorParamFns.add(bc -> Optional.ofNullable(bc.consume(buildItemClass)));
}
```

`Optional.ofNullable()` always returns either `Optional.of(value)` or `Optional.empty()` — **never null**.

